LSE-listed Kenmare Resources, which operates the Moma titanium minerals mine, in northern Mozambique, has appointed Dr Elaine Dorward-King as nonexecutive director, with immediate effect. In conjunction with her appointment to the board, Dorward-King also becomes a member of Kenmare’s sustainability committee. Dorward-King has over 30 years’ experience in the mining, chemicals and engineering industries, including the mineral sands sector. She joins Kenmare after having served as the executive VP of sustainability and external relations for gold miner Newmont Goldcorp.